{
  "text": "Comparing the effects of SC ODN on HER -2 level ( Fig 2 ) and cell survival (Fig 3 ) , one can conclude that the latter is somewhat more sensitive to treatment by the SC ODN. This is likely to be a consequence of the ability of the phosphorothioate ODN to interact with heparinbinding cell -surface receptors and other proteins in a non -sequence specific manner. [CITATION_1] Despite this, there is still a significant difference in the percent of cell survival between treatment with AS ODN and SC ODNs in all of the tumor cell lines, with the exception of MCF7, indicating that the observed response is due primarily to a sequence-specific, antisense effect.",
